$ link /SUBSYSTEM

The `/SUBSYSTEM` option specifies the *subsystem* of the resulting executable or → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/DLL[dll].

Depending on the chosen subsystem, the linker chooses an entrypoint (which can be overwritten with → Windows/development/Visual-Studio/link/options/entry[/ENTRY]).

Possible subsystems include
 • BOOT_APPLICATION
 • CONSOLE 
 • EFI_APPLICATION
 • EFI_BOOT_SERVICE_DRIVER
 • EFI_ROM
 • EFI_RUNTIME_DRIVER
 • NATIVE
 • POSIX
 • WINDOWS
